title: Coorina/CROCODILE ROCK

headings.text: ABOUT US            CONTACT US           searcH        Media

paragraphs: Along the 600m contour, as well as The Lookout at the Springs, the expansive cave shelter of Rocky Whelan, Sphinx Rock, White Rock, Black Rock—and many other outcrops— is Crocodile Rock. You pass below Crocodile Rock on Hunters Track. Looking absolutely nothing like a crocodile, it is far better understood  as a sandstone buttress rich in white quartz cemented  during the Triassic-era millions of years past.
Its heritage value is Social. It appears on Hodgman’s famous 1930s map of the mountain’s features.
